question.title: Dockerfile Not Found During Deployment to Render from GitHub Repository
question.body:
I am trying to deploy my Spring Boot application to Render using a Dockerfile. My Dockerfile is located at the root of my project directory, but I am encountering an error during the deployment process.

Steps Taken:

1- Verified that the Dockerfile is named Dockerfile and is located in the root directory of the project. 2- Tested the Dockerfile locally using docker build -t quantumweb ., which works without issues.

Despite these steps, I still encounter the error where the Dockerfile cannot be found during the deployment process. Any insights or suggestions on how to resolve this issue would be greatly appreciated.
